  "texts": [
    "Just as similar examples merge into concepts, nearby positions can aggregate into coarser regions of space.",
    "Through this equivalence, we can translate the prediction about example information per spike (Fig. 5A) into a prediction about spatial tuning (Fig.",
    "During denser theta phases, place fields should be broader, which corresponds to lower position information per spike.",
    "This prediction relies on our claim that the theta oscillation in CA3 acts as the inhibitory threshold of our model.",
    "A priori, the alternative prediction that place fields are sharper during dense theta phases is an equally valid hypothesis."
